{
  "texts": [
    "We thus present a surrogate optimization problem for Problem (P-CA):maximize π ∈ Π E x [ E y ∼ π [ r(x, y)]] -β E x [ D KL (π(• | x) ∥ π ref (• | x))] (U-CA)subject to E x [ E y ∼ π [ h i (x, y)]] ≥ 0, for all i = 1,..., m.Let the solution of Problem (U-CA) be π ⋆ and the primal value of Problem (U-CA) be P ⋆.",
    "When any policy π ∈ Π can be represented by π θ for some θ ∈ Θ, Problem (U-CA) works as a special case of Problem (P-CA).",
    "Importantly, Problem (U-CA) is a convex optimization problem, since the expectation is linear and the KL divergence is convex in the distribution π(• | x) over responses.",
    "Thus, we can introduce the Lagrangian duality in convex optimization theory [5] for Problem (U-CA).Denote the Lagrangian for Problem (U-CA) as L(π, λ) whose formula is (1) with replacement of π θ by π.",
    "The associated dual function is given by D(λ):= maximize π ∈ Π L(π, λ), which is achieved at the Lagrangian maximizer π ⋆ (λ)."
  ]
}